  DIRS [Dn:][path>][filename]

Low Memory, Internal

Lists files on drive Dn: using the
path and the specified file pattern.
Unlike the DIR command, the DIRS
command uses the Atari DOS 2 style
format. If no file name pattern is
provided, all entries of the current
directory are listed automatically.

A parameter list is not supported by
the internal version of this command.
